SPRUCE GROVE, AB — The mother of two boys killed by their father in a murder-suicide earlier this week took to Facebook to clarify the custody arrangement between her and the father.In a post on Facebook responding to a story in the Edmonton Journal, Tracy Stark said she had full custody of her sons Ryder, 13, and Radek, 11, MacDougall with their stepfather Brent Stark. Ryder and Radek were found dead in a home in Spruice Grove on Monday by their stepfather Brent Stark. The body of their father Corry MacDougall, 39, was also found in the home. RCMP have confirmed the death was a murder-suicide committed by Corry.“I will clear one thing up … this monster didn’t have primary care!!! He was given one school year with these boys so they could play hockey in Spruce Grove … I raised these babies with my husband Brent in Whitecourt their entire lives … he had 4 months with them and he took them away,” Stark wrote on Facebook.Insp. Gibson Glavin with the  wouldn’t comment on how the boys died.
“The adult was responsible, criminally responsible, for the deaths of the two boys,” he told Global News on Wednesday.
